duck: Section (music) - In music, a section is "a complete, but not independent musical idea".
Section (military unit) - A section is a small military unit in some armies.
Section (botany) - In botany, a section is a taxonomic rank below the genus, but above the species.
Memory segment, a division of computer memory
section definition: the action or an instance of cutting or separating by cutting.
Histological section, a thin slice of tissue used for microscopic examination
Caesarean section, surgical technique to facilitate child birth
Sectioning, also known outside the United Kingdom as involuntary commitment

Archaeological section - In archaeology a section is a view in part of the archaeological sequence showing it in the vertical plane, as a cross section, and thereby illustrating its profile and stratigraphy.
